<DocLayout title="Interface &amp; Action Types" activeSection="interfaces">

  <h1 class="doc-title">Interface &amp; Action Types</h1>

  <h2 class="section-heading" id="common-ros2-interface-data-types">Common ROS2 Interface &amp; Action Data Types</h2>
  <p>The following <code class="ph-type-inline">[data_type]</code> can be used for either message variables, request/response parameters, goals, results, or feedback structures.</p>
  
  <div class="table-container">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>ROS 2 Field Type</th>
          <th>C++ Equivalent</th>
          <th>Python Equivalent</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>bool</td>
          <td><code>bool</code></td>
          <td><code>bool</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>byte / char</td>
          <td><code>int8_t</code> / <code>uint8_t</code></td>
          <td><code>bytes</code> / <code>int</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>float32 / float64</td>
          <td><code>float</code> / <code>double</code></td>
          <td><code>float</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>int8 / uint8</td>
          <td><code>int8_t</code> / <code>uint8_t</code></td>
          <td><code>int</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>int16 / uint16</td>
          <td><code>int16_t</code> / <code>uint16_t</code></td>
          <td><code>int</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>int32 / uint32</td>
          <td><code>int32_t</code> / <code>uint32_t</code></td>
          <td><code>int</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>int64 / uint64</td>
          <td><code>int64_t</code> / <code>uint64_t</code></td>
          <td><code>int</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>string</td>
          <td><code>std::string</code></td>
          <td><code>str</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><em>Type[]</em> (Arrays)</td>
          <td><code>std::vector&lt;Type&gt;</code></td>
          <td><code>list</code></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>


  <h2 class="section-heading" id="structure-of-interfaces">Structure of Interfaces &amp; Action Types</h2>
  <p>Interfaces are organized by packages, and then by messages (<code>msg</code>), services (<code>srv</code>), or actions (<code>action</code>).</p>

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">Message Interfaces</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={msgInterfaceCode} lang="bash" customHtml={msgInterfaceCustom} />

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">Service Interfaces</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={srvInterfaceCode} lang="bash" customHtml={srvInterfaceCustom} />

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">Action Types</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={actionInterfaceCode} lang="bash" customHtml={actionInterfaceCustom} />


  <h2 class="section-heading" id="using-interfaces-actions">Using Interfaces &amp; Actions</h2>

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">Common Standard ROS 2 Interfaces</h3>
  <p>Before making a custom ROS 2 interface, verify if the functionality you require already exists within an interface already packaged with ROS 2.</p>
  
  <div class="table-container">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Package Name</th>
          <th>Interface Type</th>
          <th>Common Purpose</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>std_msgs</code></td>
          <td>msg</td>
          <td>Primitive wrappers (Bool, Int32, Float64, String, etc.)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>geometry_msgs</code></td>
          <td>msg</td>
          <td>Common geometric primitives (Point, Pose, Vector3, Twist, Transform)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>sensor_msgs</code></td>
          <td>msg</td>
          <td>Sensor outputs (Image, LaserScan, Imu, JointState, PointCloud2)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>nav_msgs</code></td>
          <td>msg / srv</td>
          <td>Navigation data structures (Odometry, OccupancyGrid, Path, GetPlan)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>std_srvs</code></td>
          <td>srv</td>
          <td>Basic atomic services (Empty, SetBool, Trigger)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>action_msgs</code></td>
          <td>msg</td>
          <td>Goal statuses and tracking structures utilized by actions</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">Importing Interfaces &amp; Actions Into Nodes</h3>
  <p>You must import interfaces within node scripts. <strong>Don't forget to add the packages which your interfaces come from to the dependencies of your own package under its <code>CMakeLists.txt</code> and <code>package.xml</code> files.</strong></p>

  <h4 class="subsubsection-heading">Python</h4>
  <p>For subscribers or publishers:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={pyImportMsgCode} lang="python" customHtml={pyImportMsgCustom} />

  <p>For servers or clients:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={pyImportSrvCode} lang="python" customHtml={pyImportSrvCustom} />

  <p>For action servers &amp; action clients:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={pyImportActionCode} lang="python" customHtml={pyImportActionCustom} />

  <blockquote>
    <strong>NOTE:</strong> <code class="ph-type-inline">[msg_type]</code>, <code class="ph-type-inline">[srv_type]</code> or <code class="ph-type-inline">[action_type]</code> will be simply the name of the .msg, .srv or .action file - <strong>first letters in every word are capitalized and there are no underscores (PascalCase).</strong>
    <br /><br />
    Example: <code>SensorStatus</code>
  </blockquote>

  <hr class="section-divider" />

  <h4 class="subsubsection-heading">C++</h4>
  <p>For subscribers or publishers:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={cppIncludeMsgCode} lang="cpp" customHtml={cppIncludeMsgCustom} />

  <p>For servers or clients:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={cppIncludeSrvCode} lang="cpp" customHtml={cppIncludeSrvCustom} />

  <p>For action servers &amp; action clients:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={cppIncludeActionCode} lang="cpp" customHtml={cppIncludeActionCustom} />

  <blockquote>
    <strong>NOTE:</strong> In <code>#include</code> paths, <strong>the interface name must be all-lowercase and the words separated by underscores (snake_case)</strong>. More specifically, the words that were PascalCase when creating the file name are converted to lowercase snake_case for the <code>.hpp</code> header filename.
    <br /><br />
    Example: <code>#include "custom_interfaces/msg/sensor_status.hpp"</code>
  </blockquote>

  <blockquote>
    <strong>NOTE:</strong> In <code>#include</code> paths, words separated by numbers within the interface name will not have underscores between them.
    <br /><br />
    Example (Message type is <code>custom_interfaces/msg/Pose3dFeedback</code>):<br />
    <code>#include "custom_interfaces/msg/pose3d_feedback.hpp"</code>
  </blockquote>

  <blockquote>
    <strong>NOTE:</strong> While referencing the interfaces in the C++ program block, <strong>the scoped types use PascalCase matching the original file name</strong>.
    <br /><br />
    Example: <code>custom_interfaces::msg::SensorStatus</code>
  </blockquote>


